{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1043,"text":"What an intriguing\ngroup of individuals you are ..."},{"time":5505,"text":"to a psychologist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6977,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":8440,"text":"I've had the opportunity\nover the last couple of days"},{"time":11570,"text":"of listening in on some\nof your conversations"},{"time":14984,"text":"and watching you interact with each other."},{"time":17174,"text":"And I think it's fair to say, already,"},{"time":19723,"text":"that there are 47 people in this audience,"},{"time":25494,"text":"at this moment,"},{"time":27414,"text":"displaying psychological symptoms\nI would like to discuss today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31571,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":32942,"text":"And I thought you might\nlike to know who you are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35968,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":37415,"text":"But instead of pointing at you,"},{"time":39126,"text":"which would be gratuitous and intrusive,"},{"time":42865,"text":"I thought I would tell you\na few facts and stories,"},{"time":45890,"text":"in which you may catch\na glimpse of yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50089,"text":"I'm in the field of research\nknown as personality psychology,"},{"time":54349,"text":"which is part of a larger\npersonality science"},{"time":57813,"text":"which spans the full spectrum,\nfrom neurons to narratives."},{"time":63337,"text":"And what we try to do,"},{"time":65601,"text":"in our own way,"},{"time":67188,"text":"is to make sense of how each of us --"},{"time":70793,"text":"each of you --"},{"time":72467,"text":"is, in certain respects,"},{"time":74569,"text":"like all other people,"},{"time":76993,"text":"like some other people"},{"time":79243,"text":"and like no other person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82579,"text":"Now, already you may\nbe saying of yourself,"},{"time":85770,"text":"\"I'm not intriguing."},{"time":89597,"text":"I am the 46th most boring person\nin the Western Hemisphere.\""},{"time":95895,"text":"Or you may say of yourself,"},{"time":98208,"text":"\"I am intriguing,"},{"time":101252,"text":"even if I am regarded by most people\nas a great, thundering twit.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":105227,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":106441,"text":"But it is your self-diagnosed boringness\nand your inherent \"twitiness\""},{"time":112325,"text":"that makes me, as a psychologist,\nreally fascinated by you."},{"time":117172,"text":"So let me explain why this is so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120284,"text":"One of the most influential approaches\nin personality science"},{"time":124469,"text":"is known as trait psychology,"},{"time":126083,"text":"and it aligns you along five dimensions\nwhich are normally distributed,"},{"time":131476,"text":"and that describe universally held aspects\nof difference between people."},{"time":139379,"text":"They spell out the acronym OCEAN."},{"time":142105,"text":"So, \"O\" stands for \"open to experience,\""},{"time":145180,"text":"versus those who are more closed."},{"time":147555,"text":"\"C\" stands for \"conscientiousness,\""},{"time":150754,"text":"in contrast to those with a more\nlackadaisical approach to life."},{"time":154422,"text":"\"E\" -- \"extroversion,\" in contrast\nto more introverted people."},{"time":159089,"text":"\"A\" -- \"agreeable individuals,\""},{"time":161805,"text":"in contrast to those\ndecidedly not agreeable."},{"time":165599,"text":"And \"N\" -- \"neurotic individuals,\""},{"time":168267,"text":"in contrast to those who are more stable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172268,"text":"All of these dimensions have\nimplications for our well-being,"},{"time":175682,"text":"for how our life goes."},{"time":178762,"text":"And so we know that, for example,"},{"time":181135,"text":"openness and conscientiousness\nare very good predictors of life success,"},{"time":186829,"text":"but the open people achieve that success\nthrough being audacious"},{"time":191230,"text":"and, occasionally, odd."},{"time":194077,"text":"The conscientious people\nachieve it through sticking to deadlines,"},{"time":198466,"text":"to persevering, as well as\nhaving some passion."},{"time":203662,"text":"Extroversion and agreeableness\nare both conducive"},{"time":207572,"text":"to working well with people."},{"time":210866,"text":"Extroverts, for example,\nI find intriguing."},{"time":213878,"text":"With my classes, I sometimes\ngive them a basic fact"},{"time":216885,"text":"that might be revealing\nwith respect to their personality:"},{"time":220356,"text":"I tell them that it is virtually\nimpossible for adults"},{"time":225426,"text":"to lick the outside of their own elbow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229287,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":230565,"text":"Did you know that?"},{"time":233505,"text":"Already, some of you have tried\nto lick the outside of your own elbow."},{"time":237718,"text":"But extroverts amongst you"},{"time":239518,"text":"are probably those\nwho have not only tried,"},{"time":242153,"text":"but they have successfully\nlicked the elbow"},{"time":244667,"text":"of the person sitting next to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246382,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":247408,"text":"Those are the extroverts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249117,"text":"Let me deal in a bit more detail\nwith extroversion,"},{"time":252560,"text":"because it's consequential\nand it's intriguing,"},{"time":255543,"text":"and it helps us understand\nwhat I call our three natures."},{"time":259048,"text":"First, our biogenic nature --\nour neurophysiology."},{"time":262743,"text":"Second, our sociogenic or second nature,"},{"time":266279,"text":"which has to do with the cultural\nand social aspects of our lives."},{"time":270744,"text":"And third, what makes you\nindividually you -- idiosyncratic --"},{"time":278190,"text":"what I call your \"idiogenic\" nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281260,"text":"Let me explain."},{"time":284901,"text":"One of the things that characterizes\nextroverts is they need stimulation."},{"time":288971,"text":"And that stimulation can be achieved\nby finding things that are exciting:"},{"time":293719,"text":"loud noises, parties\nand social events here at TED --"},{"time":297780,"text":"you see the extroverts\nforming a magnetic core."},{"time":301031,"text":"They all gather together."},{"time":302714,"text":"And I've seen you."},{"time":304153,"text":"The introverts are more likely\nto spend time in the quiet spaces"},{"time":307500,"text":"up on the second floor,"},{"time":309347,"text":"where they are able\nto reduce stimulation --"},{"time":313163,"text":"and may be misconstrued\nas being antisocial,"},{"time":317122,"text":"but you're not necessarily antisocial."},{"time":321310,"text":"It may be that you simply realize\nthat you do better"},{"time":325436,"text":"when you have a chance\nto lower that level of stimulation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330998,"text":"Sometimes it's an internal\nstimulant, from your body."},{"time":335170,"text":"Caffeine, for example, works much better\nwith extroverts than it does introverts."},{"time":340109,"text":"When extroverts come into the office\nat nine o'clock in the morning"},{"time":343312,"text":"and say, \"I really need a cup of coffee,\""},{"time":346221,"text":"they're not kidding --"},{"time":347396,"text":"they really do."},{"time":349531,"text":"Introverts do not do as well,"},{"time":351361,"text":"particularly if the tasks\nthey're engaged in --"},{"time":354913,"text":"and they've had some coffee --"},{"time":356482,"text":"if those tasks are speeded,"},{"time":358644,"text":"and if they're quantitative,"},{"time":360547,"text":"introverts may give the appearance\nof not being particularly quantitative."},{"time":365580,"text":"But it's a misconstrual."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367244,"text":"So here are the consequences\nthat are really quite intriguing:"},{"time":370312,"text":"we're not always what seem to be,"},{"time":372419,"text":"and that takes me to my next point."},{"time":376196,"text":"I should say, before getting to this,"},{"time":378776,"text":"something about sexual intercourse,"},{"time":381480,"text":"although I may not have time."},{"time":383605,"text":"And so, if you would like me to --"},{"time":386501,"text":"yes, you would?"},{"time":387676,"text":"OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388851,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":389960,"text":"There are studies done"},{"time":391144,"text":"on the frequency with which\nindividuals engage in the conjugal act,"},{"time":397406,"text":"as broken down by male, female;\nintrovert, extrovert."},{"time":401100,"text":"So I ask you:"},{"time":402275,"text":"How many times per minute --"},{"time":405162,"text":"oh, I'm sorry, that was a rat study --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":407070,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":410151,"text":"How many times per month"},{"time":414715,"text":"do introverted men engage in the act?"},{"time":418486,"text":"3.0."},{"time":419900,"text":"Extroverted men?"},{"time":421556,"text":"More or less?"},{"time":423616,"text":"Yes, more."},{"time":425607,"text":"5.5 -- almost twice as much."},{"time":429264,"text":"Introverted women: 3.1."},{"time":431856,"text":"Extroverted women?"},{"time":433476,"text":"Frankly, speaking as an introverted male,"},{"time":436846,"text":"which I will explain later --"},{"time":438607,"text":"they are heroic."},{"time":440973,"text":"7.5."},{"time":443782,"text":"They not only handle\nall the male extroverts,"},{"time":446158,"text":"they pick up a few introverts as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448275,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":450195,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":456796,"text":"We communicate differently,\nextroverts and introverts."},{"time":462576,"text":"Extroverts, when they interact,"},{"time":464106,"text":"want to have lots of social encounter\npunctuated by closeness."},{"time":468595,"text":"They'd like to stand close\nfor comfortable communication."},{"time":472547,"text":"They like to have a lot of eye contact,"},{"time":474770,"text":"or mutual gaze."},{"time":477241,"text":"We found in some research"},{"time":478472,"text":"that they use more diminutive terms\nwhen they meet somebody."},{"time":481873,"text":"So when an extrovert meets a Charles,"},{"time":484610,"text":"it rapidly becomes \"Charlie,\"\nand then \"Chuck,\""},{"time":487519,"text":"and then \"Chuckles Baby.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":489222,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":491032,"text":"Whereas for introverts,"},{"time":492461,"text":"it remains \"Charles,\" until he's given\na pass to be more intimate"},{"time":497390,"text":"by the person he's talking to."},{"time":500044,"text":"We speak differently."},{"time":504934,"text":"Extroverts prefer black-and-white,\nconcrete, simple language."},{"time":511854,"text":"Introverts prefer --\nand I must again tell you"},{"time":515672,"text":"that I am as extreme an introvert\nas you could possibly imagine --"},{"time":520853,"text":"we speak differently."},{"time":522594,"text":"We prefer contextually complex,"},{"time":526613,"text":"contingent,"},{"time":528569,"text":"weasel-word sentences --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530609,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":531656,"text":"More or less."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533385,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":534845,"text":"As it were."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536069,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":537108,"text":"Not to put too fine a point upon it --"},{"time":539848,"text":"like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541955,"text":"When we talk,"},{"time":543381,"text":"we sometimes talk past each other."},{"time":545724,"text":"I had a consulting contract\nI shared with a colleague"},{"time":548376,"text":"who's as different from me\nas two people can possibly be."},{"time":551739,"text":"First, his name is Tom."},{"time":554499,"text":"Mine isn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555737,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":557032,"text":"Secondly, he's six foot five."},{"time":558987,"text":"I have a tendency not to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560963,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":562030,"text":"And thirdly, he's as extroverted\na person as you could find."},{"time":565777,"text":"I am seriously introverted."},{"time":568670,"text":"I overload so much,"},{"time":570389,"text":"I can't even have a cup of coffee\nafter three in the afternoon"},{"time":575227,"text":"and expect to sleep in the evening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578178,"text":"We had seconded to this project\na fellow called Michael."},{"time":583320,"text":"And Michael almost brought\nthe project to a crashing halt."},{"time":588528,"text":"So the person who seconded him\nasked Tom and me,"},{"time":593244,"text":"\"What do you make of Michael?\""},{"time":594727,"text":"Well, I'll tell you\nwhat Tom said in a minute."},{"time":597021,"text":"He spoke in classic \"extrovert-ese.\""},{"time":599955,"text":"And here is how extroverted ears\nheard what I said,"},{"time":603554,"text":"which is actually pretty accurate."},{"time":605531,"text":"I said, \"Well Michael does have\na tendency at times"},{"time":610385,"text":"of behaving in a way\nthat some of us might see"},{"time":614489,"text":"as perhaps more assertive\nthan is normally called for.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":618941,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":621611,"text":"Tom rolled his eyes and he said,"},{"time":623412,"text":"\"Brian, that's what I said:"},{"time":626629,"text":"he's an asshole!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":628053,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":630254,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":633509,"text":"Now, as an introvert,"},{"time":634800,"text":"I might gently allude to certain\n\"assholic\" qualities"},{"time":640005,"text":"in this man's behavior,"},{"time":641324,"text":"but I'm not going to lunge for the a-word."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644152,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":647228,"text":"But the extrovert says,"},{"time":648518,"text":"\"If he walks like one, if he talks\nlike one, I call him one.\""},{"time":651416,"text":"And we go past each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653498,"text":"Now is this something\nthat we should be heedful of?"},{"time":657488,"text":"Of course."},{"time":658678,"text":"It's important that we know this."},{"time":660286,"text":"Is that all we are?"},{"time":662670,"text":"Are we just a bunch of traits?"},{"time":665563,"text":"No, we're not."},{"time":668116,"text":"Remember, you're like some other people"},{"time":671266,"text":"and like no other person."},{"time":673487,"text":"How about that idiosyncratic you?"},{"time":676485,"text":"As Elizabeth or as George,"},{"time":679760,"text":"you may share your extroversion\nor your neuroticism."},{"time":684251,"text":"But are there some distinctively\nElizabethan features of your behavior,"},{"time":688282,"text":"or Georgian of yours,"},{"time":691732,"text":"that make us understand you\nbetter than just a bunch of traits?"},{"time":696240,"text":"That make us love you?"},{"time":699461,"text":"Not just because you're\na certain type of person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703188,"text":"I'm uncomfortable putting\npeople in pigeonholes."},{"time":707081,"text":"I don't even think pigeons\nbelong in pigeonholes."},{"time":711235,"text":"So what is it that makes us different?"},{"time":714004,"text":"It's the doings that we have\nin our life -- the personal projects."},{"time":719403,"text":"You have a personal project right now,"},{"time":721248,"text":"but nobody may know it here."},{"time":725504,"text":"It relates to your kid --"},{"time":727336,"text":"you've been back three times\nto the hospital,"},{"time":729560,"text":"and they still don't know what's wrong."},{"time":733373,"text":"Or it could be your mom."},{"time":736092,"text":"And you'd been acting out of character."},{"time":738218,"text":"These are free traits."},{"time":741521,"text":"You're very agreeable,\nbut you act disagreeably"},{"time":744625,"text":"in order to break down those barriers\nof administrative torpor"},{"time":748522,"text":"in the hospital,"},{"time":749697,"text":"to get something\nfor your mom or your child."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753814,"text":"What are these free traits?"},{"time":755345,"text":"They're where we enact a script"},{"time":757939,"text":"in order to advance\na core project in our lives."},{"time":761744,"text":"And they are what matters."},{"time":763826,"text":"Don't ask people what type you are;"},{"time":766742,"text":"ask them, \"What are your core\nprojects in your life?\""},{"time":769520,"text":"And we enact those free traits."},{"time":771328,"text":"I'm an introvert,"},{"time":772667,"text":"but I have a core project,\nwhich is to profess."},{"time":777640,"text":"I'm a professor."},{"time":779798,"text":"And I adore my students,"},{"time":783080,"text":"and I adore my field."},{"time":784691,"text":"And I can't wait to tell them\nabout what's new, what's exciting,"},{"time":791366,"text":"what I can't wait to tell them about."},{"time":793642,"text":"And so I act in an extroverted way,"},{"time":795486,"text":"because at eight in the morning,"},{"time":797038,"text":"the students need a little bit of humor,"},{"time":799406,"text":"a little bit of engagement\nto keep them going"},{"time":802152,"text":"in arduous days of study."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804277,"text":"But we need to be very careful"},{"time":806456,"text":"when we act protractedly out of character."},{"time":810679,"text":"Sometimes we may find\nthat we don't take care of ourselves."},{"time":817309,"text":"I find, for example, after a period\nof pseudo-extroverted behavior,"},{"time":821947,"text":"I need to repair somewhere on my own."},{"time":825916,"text":"As Susan Cain said in her \"Quiet\" book,"},{"time":829059,"text":"in a chapter that featured\nthe strange Canadian professor"},{"time":832055,"text":"who was teaching at the time at Harvard,"},{"time":835145,"text":"I sometimes go to the men's room"},{"time":836829,"text":"to escape the slings and arrows\nof outrageous extroverts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841069,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":842177,"text":"I remember one particular day\nwhen I was retired to a cubicle,"},{"time":848573,"text":"trying to avoid overstimulation."},{"time":851117,"text":"And a real extrovert came\nin beside me -- not right in my cubicle,"},{"time":856388,"text":"but in the next cubicle over --"},{"time":858367,"text":"and I could hear various\nevacuatory noises,"},{"time":860714,"text":"which we hate -- even our own,"},{"time":863007,"text":"that's why we flush\nduring as well as after."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865761,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":868360,"text":"And then I heard\nthis gravelly voice saying,"},{"time":872974,"text":"\"Hey, is that Dr. Little?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":875433,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":878664,"text":"If anything is guaranteed\nto constipate an introvert for six months,"},{"time":885055,"text":"it's talking on the john."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":888094,"text":"That's where I'm going now."},{"time":890696,"text":"Don't follow me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":892564,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893767,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}